'''eth''' (''plural:'' '''[[eths]]''')
# A letter (''capital'' '''Ð''', ''small'' '''ð''') introduced into Old English to represent its [[dental]] [[fricative]], then not distinguished from the letter [[thorn]], no longer used in English but in still in modern use in Icelandic, [[Faroese]], and phonetics to represent the [[voiced]] [[dental]] [[fricative]] "th" sound as in the English word '''''th''en'''.

